ction of its cityscape. This book tells the story of its inhabitants, now forced to reconsider their futures. Building on recent theoretical work, it advances a new anthropological approach to time, allowing us to investigate the postindustrial era and the futures it has supposedly lost.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCoal industryzGermanyzHoyerswerda. 0aDeindustrializationzGermany. 0aShrinking citieszGermanyzHoyerswerda. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aanthropological approach.  aanthropology.  acareer.  acitizens.  acity life.  acoal industry.  acontemporary.  acultural.  adecline.  aengaging.  agerman history.  agerman reunification.  ahistorical.  ahistory of anthropology.  ahistory of germany.  ahoyerswerda.  ahuman condition.  aindustry.  alifetime.  aoutmigration.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  apostindustrial era.  apostindustrial.  aretrospective.  asocial issues.  asocial science.  asocialist model city.  asocialist model.  asociology.  aurban community.  aurban sociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311099811540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785337994?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785337994423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785337994/original  a978-3-11-099811-5  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK